TabMaid automatically closes stale tabs across Chrome, keeping you on task and freeing your RAM along the way. 

What's a stale tab? Any tab that is no longer useful to you! 
Ex) Tabs that launched Zoom meetings, Google search results more than 5 minutes old, or duplicate copies of the tab you just opened

Permissions Explanation
====================
- Access to browsing history is required to enable your personal TabMaid to know which tabs are already open so she can close them when you open a new instance of the same tab
